                        <article>
<div><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: medium;">First of all, <a href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/2639/magic-ninja-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener norewrite">Reborner's guide</a>, even if a bit outdated now, is well made and full of truths o.o)/&nbsp;<br />Although, I'd want to make something more theoric, with detailed informations about skills and gameplays...and stuff &gt;.&gt;<br /><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><u style="color: #ff0000; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: xx-large;">About "Magic" ninja</span></u><br /></span>
<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: medium;"><br /></span></span>
<div style="text-align: center;">What's the purpose of this? Well, being magic ninja at first meant to use the <strong><u>magic</u></strong> skills ninjas are given.&nbsp;</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">Nowadays, some people may refer to "magic" ninja as the "Silent Killing"-focused ones, which isn't really right because SK is <strong><u>not</u></strong>&nbsp;a magic skill, but isn't totally wrong either since a regular magic ninja using a Throwing weapon will have decent SK damages, and that still being a magic ninja after Lv300 is pretty rare (and not advised damages-wise, even with Phantom Flame highering magic, without the Lv340 skills)<br />Although, the Lv340 skills might separate these three or four type of ninjas more clearly: Physical focused, SK focused, Magic focused.<br />And of course, Hybrid ones. Which is (I think) the first purpose of Ninjas.</div>
</div>
</div>
<div><a style="display: none;"></a>
<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #0029ff; font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: 300%;"><strong><u>BUILDS</u></strong></span></div>
</div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">
<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: medium;">"&gt;"&nbsp;means "then"&nbsp;<br />"<strong>/</strong>"&nbsp;means the choice or order is up to you</span><u style="color: #b919e6;"><strong><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Magic ninja builds (Throwing/Staff)</span></strong></u></div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="center"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: large;"><br /><u>INT&gt;DEX&gt;VIT </u>(for Struggler)<u>&gt;BL/GR,</u> then <u>CRT</u> or <u>VIT</u> or <u>AGI</u><br /></span></span><span style="font-family: &quot;font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Probably the most effective of all the magic builds, as in the one giving the most MATK.</span></span><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: large;"><u><br /></u></span></span></div>
<div align="center">
