<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #0029ff; font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: 300%;"><strong><u>SKILLS</u></strong></span></div>
</div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><strong style="font-size: medium; text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><br /></span></strong><span style="color: #000000; font-size: medium;">To become ninja, you need to complete a quest from Suigetsu at Minaula castle, available from Lv100+, collecting:<br />-20 Black Feather (Crow Samurai)<br />-20 Small shells (Kappa)<br />-20 Fan Feather (Tengu)<br />-20 Broken Flame Blower (Fire Cat)<br />Class Requirement: </span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="color: #4ae619;">None. (You just can't be Ninja already or Samurai. Become another special class first to do the quest again.)</span><br /></span><strong style="color: #000000; font-size: medium; text-decoration: underline;"><br /></strong><span style="color: #ff0000; font-size: large;"><strong><u>Skills not out yet might be mispelled or/and misinterpreted.</u>&nbsp;<br /><u>Click on "Quest:" to see skill quests requirements</u></strong></span><br /></span><strong style="color: #ff0000; font-family: &quot;font-size:large;">Also, modifications on-going on Japanese version, see at the end of the section.</strong><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #000000;"><br /><u><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Shuriken Mastery:</span></u></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Passive skill boosting ATK and MATK when using a Throwing weapon.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 1 - Ninja class change&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 2 - Item at Drafbourg:Immigrant Ward from Matif, Level 220 required</span><br /><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">SLv1: ATK+50, MATK+100</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">SLv2: ATK+90, MATK+180 (※ +40 ATK, +80 MATK Compared to Lv1.)</span><strong style="color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;"><br /></strong><br /><strong style="color: #000000;"><u>Kyuseijutsu Yang:</u></strong><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Obtain the power of Yang. Enhance the effects of Tonjutsu and magic power. Possibility of creating 3 clones with Bunshin no Jutsu while the buff is active.</span><br />Level 1 - Item at Minaula city from Suigetsu or ninja class change (MP1)<br /><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Effects:</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">- Add [Yangton] effect and clones disappear.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">- If you have learned [Phantom Flame], [Phantom Flame] is renewed.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">- If [Yinton] is applied, it will be removed.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">- Triggers [Combo Stock] randomly during the effective time.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">- When using the skills designated by [Combo Stock], the damage of thoses skills AKA [Katon no Jutsu], [Suiton no Jutsu], [Raiton no Jutsu] and [Doton no Jutsu], increase.<br />- MaxMP + 500<br />- MATK + 20</span></span></span><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="color: #000000;"><br /><br /></span><strong><u>Kyuseijutsu Yin:</u></strong><br />Obtain the power of Yin. Enhance the effects and resistance of clones.&nbsp;Possibility of creating 3 clones with Bunshin no Jutsu while the buff is active.<br />Level 1 - Item at Minaula city from Suigetsu or ninja class change (MP1)<br /><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br />Effects:<br />- Add [Yinton] effect and 3 clones.<br /></span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: &quot;font-size:medium;">- If you have learned [Phantom Flame], [Phantom Flame] is renewed.<br /></span><span style="font-family: &quot;font-size:medium;">- If [Yangton] is applied, it will be removed.<br />- MaxHP + 1000&nbsp;<br /></span><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';">- Recover 1000 HP.<br />- Evasion +10%&nbsp;<br /></span></span><span style="font-family: 'times new roman'; font-size: medium;">- Allows Silent Killing to deal critical damages.</span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><br /><br /><strong style="color: #000000;"><u>Ni Rengeki:</u></strong><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Passive skill allowing you to get a double atk from a normal hit. Doesn&rsquo;t work if your weapon has an autoskill.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 1 - Ninja class change&nbsp;<br /></span><span style="color: #000000;">Level 2 - Item at Minaula city from Sawa, Level 240 required</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;"><br /><strong style="text-decoration: underline;">Bunshin no Jutsu:</strong></span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Creates 3 clones to protect yourself. You can&rsquo;t go over 3 clones with this skill, and you can only create 2 clones when paralyzed. Clones aren&rsquo;t available when stunned or blinded. MP is required to keep clones while fighting.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 1 -Ninja class change (MP128)</span><br /><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">-Even at max DEX, <strong>need -2 seconds</strong><u> delay</u> from equipments to reduce it at minimum (1 second) <br />-Each clone drains 1% of MaxMP per second during battle. 3 clones = 3% per second.</span><br /><strong style="color: #000000;"><u><br /></u></strong><strong style="color: #000000;"><u>Desperate Move:<br /></u></strong><span style="color: #000000;">Heals your HP, heal amount being based on your Lv. If your current HP is less than 10% of your MaxHP, you get an additional heal and 3 clones are created. Cancel MP drain from clones and gives a MP regen buff.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 1 - Ninja class change (MP24)</span><br /><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br />-At 200(?) DEX, skill delay maxed (1 second) <br />-MP heal buff is fixed at 1% MaxMP per second for 10 seconds.<br /><br /><strong style="color: #000000;"><u>Dance of Clones:</u></strong><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Physical attack skill. The damages and delay are based on your critical damages and your clones amount: each clone deals damages and adds 1 second delay. Unavailable if stunned or blind.</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 1 - Quest at Minaula city from Suigetsu, Level 140 required (MP48)</span><br /><span style="color: #000000;">Level 2 - Quest at Minaula city from Suishin, Level 280 required (MP72)</span><br /></span></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;"></a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="color: #f209ee;">Quest:</span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #000000;">For SLv1:<br />- Ganei &times;1 <br />- Ippon-datara&nbsp;&times;25 <br />- Ittan-momen &times;50 <br />- Fire cat &times;75<br /><br />For SLv2:<br />- Gauchel &times;1<br />- Gigantes &times;50 <br />- Jacbos &times;50 <br />- Werewolf fur &times;5 </span><span style="color: #f209ee;">.</span></div>
