<span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="color: #f209ee;">More infos:</span><br /><strong><u>DMG formula:</u></strong><br />Domination can only give 10 different DMG (dmg with a 1/2 digit difference excluded, those are probably due to rounded values.)<br />To calculate them, you'll have to get first the Max. DMG, and then you'll deduce the other 9 as follows:<br /><br />(MATK&times;12) &times; [1+(Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100)] + Fixed magic + CRT&times;16 = X (result truncated?)<br /><br /><br />X = Maximum DMG<br /><br /><br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*1 = X1 (results rounded)<br /><br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*2<br /> = X2<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*3<br /> = X3<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*4<br /> = X4<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*5<br /> = X5<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*6<br /> = X6<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*7<br /> = X7<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*8<br /> = X8<br />X-([(MATK&times;12) &times;(1 + (Neutral magic's percentage amount &divide; 100))] &divide; 100)*9<br /> = X9<br /><br />X, X1, X2, X3, X4, X5, X6, X7, X8 and X9 are all the DMG you can get from Domination!<br /><br />-Cast time is 1 second at minimum, delay is 1 second too.&nbsp;<br />-1 CRT = +16 DMG. CRT400= +6400 DMG.<br />-Damages affected by<strong>MATK, neutral magic+%</strong> and CRT&nbsp;<br />-MP heal buff is fixed at 1% MaxMP per second for 10 seconds.<br /><br /><strong><u>Utsusemi:</u></strong><br />Passive skill giving a chance to survive with 1 HP when hit to 0 HP. Doen&rsquo;t work if damages taken are too bigs.<br />Level 1 - Quest at Kakeula city from Ryuan, Level 180 required<br /></span></span></span>
