<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="color: #0029ff; font-size: 300%;"><strong><u>HOW TO PLAY?</u></strong></span></span></div>
</div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: medium;">The way a ninja wielding a throwing weapon uses his skills <u><strong>(<em>more details about skills effects and/or formulas in the skills list!</em>)</strong></u>...</span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;"><u><strong><br /><span style="font-size: large;">FROM LV100+</span></strong></u></span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">...is the following: <br />Use the Yang buff. You'll see Katon or Raiton's icon in the top left on your screen: that's the skill you have to use. Once you used it, it will switch to the other Jutsu (so Katon&gt;Raiton or Raiton&gt;Katon). <br />Ideally, once the enemy is both burnt and paralyzed, use Earthshaker! You might want to get a good stock of MP pots if you don't have a clone set, but don't worry, this issue will be over in 120 lvls.</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><u><strong><br />Explanations:</strong></u></span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">-</span><span style="font-size: medium;"> Katon no jutsu</span><span style="font-size: medium;"> has a chance of burning the enemy. It also gives you a buff &ldquo;Reflection&rdquo;, reflecting some damages if you or your clones get hit. It deals more damages on Earth element foes.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">- </span><span style="font-size: medium;">Raiton no justsu</span><span style="font-size: medium;"> has a chance to paralyze enemies and a bit more damages than Katon.&nbsp;It deals more damages on Water element foes.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">-</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: #b919e6;"> Eart</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: #2264f0;">hs</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: #22c7f0;">ha</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: #22f0f0;">ker</span><span style="font-size: medium;"> will deal high damages with a huge, maybe even total pierce through any mdef if it's used while the enemy is burnt <strong><u>and</u></strong>&nbsp;paralyzed. If the &ldquo;burnt&rdquo; or &ldquo;paralyzed&rdquo; status came from your own skills, Earthshaker will cure it. Moreover, Earthshaker seems to be a Light&amp;Dark element skill and it will deal smaller damages against both these elements.</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />You might continue using this way of playing until either</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">1) You have enough CRT to make DoC effective as a source of DPS if you're more hybrid/physical type. You just have to make sure you have your clones, and spam DoC then x)</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />2)You level up to 220 if you're more magical type</span><br /><strong><u><span style="color: #ff0000;"><br /><span style="font-size: large;">FROM LV220+:</span></span></u></strong><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">At Lv 220+, you can get Domination: it&rsquo;s a neutral magic attack dealing great damages, only available after the use of Earthshaker. Moreover it will create 3 clones like Bunshin no justsu, even in paralyzed state and all that with a very low MP cost.Then you can do KATON&gt;RAITON&gt;EARTHSHAKER&gt;DOMINATION , or simply EARTHSHAKER&gt;DOMINATION, which is quite safe in terms of survivability, but the def pierce of Domination is way weaker than Earthshaker&rsquo;s full combo one. DPS also may suffer a little depending on your equipements (with a modest magic ninja set, i used to kill megaroches faster with full combo than with Domi spam). <br />This skill also heals MP, so if you see your MPs dropping dangerously low, you can spam it until you regain a fair amount of MP. Don't forget that clones will fade away if you run out of MPs during a battle!</span><br /><span style="font-size: large;"><br /><span style="color: #ff0000; font-weight: bold;"><u>FROM LV300+:</u></span></span><br /><span style="font-size: medium; color: #000000;">Silent Killing is a physical attack, using MATK, ATK, Crit dmgs and Elements as its damage factors. The fewer clones you have, the higher the damages.<br /></span><span style="font-size: medium;">How to play? You can:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />-Rely on AVD and spam SK until all your clones got consumed, because SK consumes 1 clone per activation, bunshin again and SK again. Then repeat.</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />-Don't rely on it, and then make sure to try to hit like this (for a maximum DPS output): SK, get hit, SK, re-clone. Why? because the fewer clones you have, the higher the dmgs will be. If a safer way of fighting is required, don't hesitate to clone as much as needed!</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />You will need about -4 second delay if you put STR instead of DEX and -1 or -2 with 256 DEX+. But don't forget bunshin no jutsu needs -2 second delay anyway...and you will use it. I guarantee it.</span><br /><strong style="font-size: medium;"><u><span style="color: #ff0000;"><br /></span></u></strong><strong><u><span style="color: #ff0000; font-size: large;">FROM LV320+:</span></u></strong><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">You just unlocked Phantom flame, congrats! But what are Phantom flame's effects? It increases SK, Katon/Raiton no jutsu and DoC damages. So here are 2 possible updates on your gameplay:<br /></span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">1)You might want to go full Dance of Clones + PF (adds "Explosion" damages over DoC)</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">You can either simply use it once when first attacking, and if the enemy isn't dead yet, spam your regular DoC afterwards. Or, if you're confident about your evasion or if you're in a party with a Tank, you can rebuff. Although Phantom Flame is fixed at 3 seconds delay, you can get the rebuff time down to 2 seconds by using Yin buff twice in a row. But beware, if you do so, it means you'll be cloneless for a second!<br /><br />2) You went the full Magic ninja route: Continue to follow the icons! Actually, you can use Katon and Raiton as your main source of DPS already and only use Earthshaker/domination to reclone and/or regain your MPs.<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong><u><span style="font-size: large;">FROM LV340+:</span></u><br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: medium;">You're still there? Well, maybe you're</span></span><span style="font-size: medium;">&nbsp;<span style="font-family: 'times new roman';">interested in your 4 new skills</span>.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: medium;">You'll have to build up Heaven &amp; Earth as well as using strengthened Jutsus. How does it work? Let le nub thread creator try to explain:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">When you use the buff Yang, a little icon will appear near your name:<br /></span><a style="font-size: medium;" href="http://www.casimages.com/img.php?i=17092603510220995415287825.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://nsm07.casimages.com/img/2017/09/26//17092603510220995415287825.jpg" /></a><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />Thanks to your new passive skill Astrological techniques, when you use the corresponding skill, the icon will change and you'll see A.T.'s icon appear, with a number on it:<br /></span><a style="font-size: medium;" href="http://www.casimages.com/img.php?i=17092603513220995415287826.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://nsm07.casimages.com/img/2017/09/26//17092603513220995415287826.jpg" /></a><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><br />Also, a "power" will appear in the middle of the screen under your HP bar:<br /></span><a style="font-size: medium;" href="http://www.casimages.com/img.php?i=17092603503120995415287823.jpg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://nsm07.casimages.com/img/2017/09/26//17092603503120995415287823.jpg" /><br /></a><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">As you can see, the "fragments" (A.T.'s icon) will go up 1 by 1 when you use the right skill, and the Power displayed 5 by 5. You can only use Heaven and Earth with a minimum (and maximum) of 10 fragments <br />The Power, from 5 to 100, will <strong>greatly</strong>&nbsp;increase both Heaven &amp; Earth and your Jutsus damages. A wrong skill (meaning, one that isnt shown near your name) will decrease Power by 15.<br />As you can see, building H&amp;E up to its maximum power is very long and most probably won't be your main source of DPS.</span></span></div>
<span style="font-family: 'times new roman';"><span style="font-size: large;"><u><strong>Some global facts about your skills:</strong></u></span><br /><span style="font-size: medium; color: #000000;">-Even at Max DEX necessary skill delay to get maxed for all your magic and jutsu skills is -2 seconds. <br />-From 200 DEX, all the casting times are maxed out.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">I put everything else in the skill list for now <img style="max-width: 100%;" src="//storage.proboards.com/forum/images/smiley/tongue.png" alt=":P" /></span><br /><br /><strong><u><span style="color: #0029ff; font-size: large;">I'll complete this guide regularly, please tell me if you have anything to add or comment about! (infos, ideas, suppositions, english mistakes of mine, typos, etc...) </span></u></strong></span></div>
